On Monday, December 03, 2007, at 12:44PM, "Courtney Hook" <courtneyhook(-at-)shaw.ca> wrote:

>Having perused the ratwell and bartnek site and other info, I'm wondering how
>to identify which wire is which for the relay. Even bartnek wasn't sure about
>this. Apparently buses have two wires to the solenoid, one for F.I. and the
>other for the ignition. Can someone identify which one is the ignition?

The ignition wire is red/black as seen in the wiring diagrams.

>Also,
>does the F.I. wire just stay where it is on the solenoid? I did my Beetle, but
>it doesn't have the F.I. wire, so it was easy.

Yes. It gets its power at that terminal from the hard start relay just like it used to directly via the ignition switch.

